explanation: Include every direct callee of process_short_param because the MISRA rule concerns any use of memcmp in code paths exercised by the target: inspect each process_param__* implementation to see whether it uses memcmp to compare null-terminated strings. Include get_param_value because several callees (process_param__threads, process_param__connections, process_param__timeout) call it — memcmp usage may be buried there. Include the library symbol memcmp so the analyzer can detect direct calls and their argument usage (to determine whether memcmp is being used to compare null‑terminated strings rather than raw byte buffers).
